⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Corridors
node TGL · TGL · ⟦The Corridors:TGL:378a75⟧

WHO   — The Corridors — the ten gauntlets of Naju
WHAT  — The in-between passages of Naju — the corridors that link the rooms of the labyrinth, run as star-Fighter gauntlets; clearing all ten is what arms the alien world's self-destruct.
WHERE — TGL · The Guardian Legend  Framework inputs: The Guardian Legend (Compile, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a labyrinth must have its passages, and these passages are trials; because the way between the rooms is paid for in fire; because to arm a world's end, every gauntlet must be cleared, one guardian-boss at a time.
HOW   — By the run itself — the hurtling flight through enemy fire, the light of the tunnel, the guardian-boss that seals each Corridor's end until it is beaten and the seal gives way.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We are the ten ways between — run us through, beat the guardian at each end, and the world's end is armed.

